  "content": "<h1>Tab: Combat</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Helvetica;\">Figuer 1: Combat Tab</span></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/tz5V6hp/Screenshot-2021-02-18-at-13-38-51.webp\" alt=\"Combat Tab\" width=\"600\" height=\"437\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">The combat tab shows all your weapons, armor, shield and ammunition.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">All weapons, armors, shield and ammunition from the Core Rules is part of the system and can be found under compendiums. Just drag/drop them onto your character sheet.<br /><br /></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Weapons:&nbsp;Image, Weapon name and any requirements and properties is listed below. Damage and Banes/Boons are also shown.<br /><br />They're 3 button to the right. Equip, Edit and Delete. If a weapon or an armor is equip and you don&rsquo;t meet the requirements the icon turns red and the system automatically adds the penalties.<br /><br /><span style=\"color: #131310; font-family: 'Apple Color Emoji';\">ðŸŽ²</span><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #131310; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;By clicking on the weapons name you can make an Attack roll.<br /><br /></span></li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Armor: Any bonuses to defense is automatically added when equipped.<br /><br /></li>\n<li class=\"p1\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Ammunition: You can left-click on the amount number to increase and right-click to decrease.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Edit Weapon</h2>\n<p>Figure 2: Edit weapon<br /><img src=\"https://i.ibb.co/zPrwNHn/Screenshot-2021-02-18-at-13-59-27.webp\" alt=\"Edit Weapon\" width=\"600\" height=\"659\" /><br /><br /></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Sometimes you need to choose with Attack Modifer you want to use. The the weapon has a Swift property you can choose between Strength or Agilty as a modifier to your attack roll.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">You can add multiple damage and damage types if need.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica;\">E.g. if a weapon has an extra 1d6 Fire damage from a spell. It will be shown as different types of damage and damage is rolled separately.</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 36px; text-indent: -36px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">Everything combat related will be covered in further detail in the Combat journal entry.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 36px; text-indent: -36px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 36px; text-indent: -36px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; text-indent: -36px;\">@JournalEntry[ZF3hE21DjzP8j9OO]{Combat}&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 36px; text-indent: -36px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</p>",
